  <cateringDescription><![CDATA[<p>The hotel serves a hot and cold buffet breakfast to get you started each morning. For dinner in the restaurant, you'll get four fantastic courses with plenty of choice. </p>
<p>If you want a change from the half board menu you can have a delicious dinner at the hotel's Brasserie La Sapiniere with 30% off their a la carte menu. All of this can be enjoyed while taking in the stunning views of Mont Blanc and the surrounding mountain range. </p>]]></cateringDescription>
  <deactivateThisPage>0</deactivateThisPage>
  <description><![CDATA[<p class="p1">Hotel Gran Baita's the perfect place if you want a bit of luxury. It was refurbished last year with modern alpine décor and stylish rooms and public areas. The staff are great and give a really attentive service so you can enjoy your holiday with everything taken care of.</p>
<p class="p1">The hotel's just outside of <a data-udi="umb://document/6001103ad3884b75a70ed71efd274ef8" href="/{localLink:umb://document/6001103ad3884b75a70ed71efd274ef8}" title="Courmayeur">Courmayeur,</a> about a ten-minute walk from the centre. When it's time to head to the slopes, or to return home after a hard day of skiing, take advantage of the free shuttle that runs from 8.30am to 5pm every day. You can also use it to pop into Courmayeur for a spot of shopping. If you do fancy the walk, it’s a great way to stretch the legs and you’ll get some great views of the surrounding area.</p>
<p class="p1">When you get back to the hotel at the end of the day, try and make some time for the fantastic spa. We love taking a dip in the heated pool before getting ready for dinner. It opens up to the outside where you can breathe in the fresh mountain air while staying warm in the water. The meals here are a real highlight. Breakfast and dinner are included and if you want to try their a la carte brasserie, you’ll get a 30% discount.</p>
<p class="p1">Transfer time: approx. 1 hour 45 mins from Turin airport.</p>]]></description>
